# Clean layer separation

Preserve **vertical boundaries**: API maps HTTP to application use cases; application owns orchestration and business rules; persistence stays behind infrastructure abstractions.

## Endpoints (`Sunday.Api`)

- **No business logic** in endpoint classes: bind route/query/body to a command, call the **command handler**, map the result to HTTP (status, headers, body).
- Do **not** inject or use **repositories**, `DbContext`, or domain rules in endpoints — only handlers (and minimal mapping/authorization wiring as appropriate).

## Command and query handlers (`Sunday.Application`)

- **Business logic belongs here**, not in endpoints.
- Do **not** inject **`I*Repository`** (or concrete repository types) into handlers. Expose data access through narrower application or domain abstractions instead of repository interfaces on the handler.

## When adding code

Prefer extending the correct layer over leaking concerns upward or downward.
